[SN]TITLE[SN]
Arrest after PC hit by off-road bike in Abertridwr

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been arrested after a police officer was hit by an off-road bike in Caerphilly county.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The driver, 41, was riding down High Street, Abertridwr, at around 20:00 BST on Wednesday when the incident happened.
He was later arrested on suspicion of assaulting a police officer and dangerous driving.
Gwent Police said the officer had minor injuries but did not need hospital treatment.
